social_posts.post_text: Feeling the urge to document more so here’s a November photo dump 🤸🏻‍♀️

December 2022 included Kerry’s first Olive Garden breadstick experience, @teammate.company growing to 10 people, an amazing Christmas dinner by @ughitsdemi, a 22 hour drive to Montana, the first office Photoshoot, and more 🤯

Top 10 Photos of 2022 📷

Currently hibernating in the mountains and reflecting on what has been an insane year of creative growth and new personal milestones!! Could not be more grateful to have toured for a few weeks, traveled for shows & shoots in NYC, Miami, Vegas, + Mexico, met some amazing new people I’ve loved creating with, and knocked off a couple big bucket list items. 

Here’s to documenting more memories, continuing to learn new camera things, and hopefully hitting the road again in 2023!! 

PS - Don’t forget that these recap posts are focused on everyone’s personal high points this year. They never show the full scope of highs and lows. Be kind to yourself while scrolling on social media rn and see you in the New Year ❤️

Spent my 32nd birthday exploring a different city, playing with my camera, buying trinkets, and watching a sunset. Then I had an excellent (although semi-embarrassing!!!!!) dinner and now I’m sitting at a little bonfire. Excellent day of getting older.

Thanks for the bday messages :) Looking forward to another year around the sun!

Caught the back half of tonight’s Live Rewind of @johnmayer’s April 2022 #SobRockTour Nashville show on @lifewithjohnmayer and it was so cool to revisit the show photos I took that night while streaming!!

Whenever I shoot a show, I typically prefer to have a ginger ale & make my selects + edit the show photos the same night in absolute silence in the back of the bus 🙃 That way I can play back some of the moments in my head and remember what I was feeling when I took a particular photo. I’ve also noticed I usually feel best about my work when I edit w this process because it seems like it helps me make better selects on which moments might stick with fans. Only people I’ve ridden with on the bus probably know this 😂 But anyway I had a similar feeling looking at these photos while listening and I thought that was cool. This has become far too long of a caption but I’m not turning back! Tysm for reading or not reading!

My 10 Favorite Photos in 2023 (In No Particular Order) 💜

It’s been a fun (but also kinda stressful??) few days going back thru all the photos I’ve taken this year, but I finally narrowed it down to 10 of my favorites. I’m really so proud of the memories I was able to capture, the different content formats I tried (like omg my footage was in a @kodak_shootfilm launch???), and the growth I can personally see in my own creative process!!

I did a lot more video & short form stuff this year and I’m so excited to see how that keeps evolving within my own journey and the entertainment industry as a whole. It’s been a fascinating new world shooting on my iPhone instead of a camera proper 😂 It’s so thrilling that we have so many different storytelling formats to tap into these days!

Very much looking forward to whatever comes my way in 2024 😁 Hope you have a restful last few days of 2023!

Also! If you’d like to see some camera settings info stuff, I’m going to post all of that over on my TikTok later today 🤸🏻‍♀️

December included a trip to NYC for the last few @jonasbrothers shows of the year, hangs with east coast friends, chicken only chicken parmigiana, hard drive back-ups, a visit to @legolandcalifornia, NYE in Lake Tahoe, and more! 

Happy New Year and here’s to 12 more photo dumps in 2024 😂

Celebrated my 33rd bday over the weekend! I love growing older. What an honor and a privilege!

Here’s 3 things I’ve been thinking about over the last few days 😁

1. Focus on the intentions of your actions rather than the specifically desired outcome. If the intentions are well-meaning, then the right outcome will come. It just might not be the one you were originally expecting.

2. I never want to stop learning. It’s so important to stay curious and continue to be a student in work, play, etc. There’s no end point!

3. The best way to learn is by doing. Pick a place, jump in, and do it kinda scared. The alternative is staying the same. Boring!

PS-  slide 2 is from my 7th bday party 💜
